  "text": "LLVM Pass Manager Registration and Execution Chain:\n\n1. PASS REGISTRATION MECHANISM:\n   The registration of LLVM optimization passes begins with the RegisterPass<> template defined in llvm/include/llvm/PassSupport.h (line 89). This template creates a PassInfo object containing metadata about the pass (name, argument, ID, constructor) and immediately registers it with the global PassRegistry via PassRegistry::getPassRegistry()->registerPass().\n\n   The PassInfo class (llvm/include/llvm/PassInfo.h) stores pass metadata including the pass name, command-line argument, type ID, and a constructor function. When a pass is registered using RegisterPass<>, the PassInfo is stored in llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h's PassRegistry, which maintains two maps: PassInfoMap (indexed by type ID) and PassInfoStringMap (indexed by argument string).\n\n2. PASSMANAGER TEMPLATE:\n   The core PassManager template is defined in llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h (line 162). It is a template class parameterized on IRUnitT (Module or Function), AnalysisManagerT, and ExtraArgTs. The PassManager maintains a vector of passes (std::vector<std::unique_ptr<PassConceptT>> Passes) and provides two key methods:\n\n   - addPass() template method (lines 193-202): Takes a pass object and wraps it in a PassModel, then stores it in the Passes vector\n   - run() method (declared at line 190, implemented in llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerImpl.h lines 28-98): Executes all passes in sequence\n\n3. POLYMORPHIC PASS EXECUTION INFRASTRUCTURE:\n   The PassConcept abstract base class (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerInternal.h, lines 40-63) defines the polymorphic interface that all passes must conform to:\n   - virtual PreservedAnalyses run(IRUnitT &IR, AnalysisManagerT &AM, ExtraArgTs... ExtraArgs) = 0\n   - virtual StringRef name() const = 0\n   - virtual bool isRequired() const = 0\n\n   The PassModel template (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerInternal.h, lines 70-114) wraps any concrete pass type and provides the polymorphic implementation by delegating to the wrapped pass's run() method (line 91).\n\n4. PASS EXECUTION FLOW:\n   The PassManager::run() implementation (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerImpl.h, lines 28-98) iterates over the Passes vector and executes each pass:\n\n   - For each pass in the Passes vector (line 67)\n   - Call PassInstrumentation callbacks before and after the pass (lines 70-84)\n   - Execute Pass->run(IR, AM, ExtraArgs...) through the PassConcept polymorphic interface (line 76)\n   - Invalidate analyses based on PreservedAnalyses returned by the pass (line 80)\n   - Accumulate preserved analyses across all passes (line 88)\n\n5. STANDARD OPTIMIZATION PIPELINE CONSTRUCTION (O2/O3):\n   The PassBuilder class (llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h) orchestrates the construction of optimization pipelines. The buildModuleOptimizationPipeline() method (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp, lines 1477-1550+) builds the standard O2/O3 optimization pipeline by:\n\n   - Creating a ModulePassManager instance (line 1481)\n   - Adding module-level passes such as PartialInlinerPass (line 1486), ReversePostOrderFunctionAttrsPass (line 1503)\n   - Adding function-level passes through a FunctionPassManager\n   - Calling addPass() on the PassManager for each optimization pass\n\n   The pipeline builder respects OptimizationLevel to determine which passes to include, enabling progressive optimization at different levels (O0, O1, O2, O3, Os, Oz).\n\n6. PASS REGISTRY DEFINITIONS:\n   The llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def file contains macro-based declarations of all available passes with their names and constructors. This file is included to register all standard LLVM passes at initialization time.\n\nThe complete registration and execution chain flows as: RegisterPass<> → PassRegistry::registerPass() → PassBuilder constructs pipeline → PassManager::addPass() wraps in PassModel → PassManager::run() executes through PassConcept polymorphic interface → Analysis invalidation and preservation tracking."
}

